spanGrp.span: ‘I think that as for the Cabecars,
Yís të (m) begetse se je kã'wak kabekar-wa
and those in our place, there are many of us and we are alike.
sa kã' ska se rö ñãebö tã'ĩ
People think that we are different,
pe të í begetse nã se rö kwãwã
but the Indians themselves know that we are the same.
Í wakwa jegeta *të [wã] í juñẽr jebi se rö ñãebö
We may speak differently; they speak differently and we speak differently;
Se je ktö-'gẽ jebönẽ (_) (_) (_) se je ktö'-gẽ rö jaulë
There are clans there that we do not know.
Ma/ jeska distö tsõ ĩã ka sulë se je wã jiebi
It is said that we are not better than they are,
Jeska í wayi-nã ka rö kuna ĩã jie-wa cha rö je köũ se je cha inga
nor that we are better than them;
o se je cha köũ jie-wa cha inga
but it was God, not us, who separated us.
ataranã Sibö nẽ të sa jula bötsá jekepi ka rö se je wã se je wakwa ñã jula bötsá jebi
God blew on us with his breath
Sibö të se je ĩã (_) se je wökwã' y jie siwã' wa
he just made corn and black corn.
kwöwö yuá-ite kwö yelë í bö
And so he spread them across the earth.
Jebi jie të í jũã'-mĩ jishögö inga
but there is nothing that can change us.
Pero ka jirö kuna të sa wömẽnẽwẽ kwãwã bi kuna
Se rö e-kka u/ e-kka uña bö
Just because of that people think that we do not underestand each other,
(_) Jebönẽ wa pe të begetse-nã ka se ĩã ksér- ra je ra je kté rö kwãwã
but it is the same language;
Je rö ñãebö í (m) í ñã wakwa bö
it is the same and it has the same name.
they speak well and we speak well too;
jemẽ jie-wa ktö'-gẽ rö bá se je ktö'-gẽ rö bá
we do not outdo them but they do not outdo us.
Jie-wa ka ktö' donã se je mẽ jie-wa ka ktö' donã se je mẽ y ka se je donã jie-wa
it was God who let us the way he wanted.
Sibö nẽ të sa wagi ka/ sa wak katatiák-ka menẽbi jie-wa í kiar kepi
And we cannot change that and be only one.
Jeska ka se mẽnẽ je (_) ktö' menẽwã-glöu-mĩ e-kka uña bö kuna
